<urn:samm:io.BatteryPass.MaterialComposition:1.2.0#BatteryMaterialList> a owl:Class,
        aas:SubmodelElementList ;
    rdfs:label "BatteryMaterials"@en ;
    rdfs:comment """"Component materials used" (No. 17.a-c): Naming the materials (as a composition of substances) in cathode, anode, electrolyte according to public standards, including specification of the corresponding component (i.e., cathode, anode, or electrolyte). We suggest a reporting threshold of 0.1 % weight by weight.

DIN DKE Spec 99100 chapter reference: 6.5.3-6.5.4"""@en .

<urn:samm:io.BatteryPass.MaterialComposition:1.2.0#HazardousSubstancesList> a owl:Class,
        aas:SubmodelElementList ;
    rdfs:label "HazardousSubstances"@en ;
    rdfs:comment """"Hazardous substances" (No 20.a-e): Name (agreed substance nomenclature, e.g. IUPAC or chemical name) all hazardous substance (as ?any substance that poses a threat to human health and the environment?). Suggested above 0.1 % weight by weight within each (sub-)component.

DIN DKE Spec 99100 chapter reference: 6.5.4 - 6.5.6"""@en .

<urn:samm:io.BatteryPass.MaterialComposition:1.2.0#ImpactList> a owl:Class,
        aas:SubmodelElementList ;
    rdfs:label "Impact"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "Impact statements based on, e.g., REACH or GHS for all hazard classes applicable to substances in the battery."@en .

:MaterialComposition_batteryChemistry a owl:Class,
        aas:SubmodelElementCollection ;
    rdfs:label "ProductChemistry"@en ;
    rdfs:comment """Composition of a product in general terms by specifying the cathode and anode active material as well as electrolyte.

DIN DKE Spec 99100 chapter reference: 6.5.2"""@en .

:MaterialComposition_batteryMaterials_batteryMaterials_batteryMaterialLocation a owl:Class,
        aas:SubmodelElementCollection ;
    rdfs:label "Location"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "Battery component that relates to the material"@en .

:MaterialComposition_hazardousSubstances_hazardousSubstances_hazardousSubstanceLocation a owl:Class,
        aas:SubmodelElementCollection ;
    rdfs:label "Location"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "Hazardous substances (No. 19-23): Location on a (sub-)component-level of all hazardous substances (as ?any substance that poses a threat to human health and the environment?). Suggested via a unique identifier or nomenclature."@en .

<urn:samm:io.BatteryPass.MaterialComposition:1.2.0#MaterialComposition/submodel> a owl:Class,
        aas:Submodel ;
    rdfs:label "MaterialComposition" ;
    rdfs:comment """Mandatory data: Battery chemistry; critical raw materials; materials used in the cathode, anode, and 
electrolyte; hazardous substances; impact of substances on the environment and on human health or 
safety

Copyright ? 2024 Circulor (for and on behalf of the Battery Pass Consortium). This work is li-censed under a Creative Commons License Attribution-NonCommercial 4.0 International (CC BY-NC 4.0). Readers may reproduce material for their own publications, as long as it is not sold com-mercially and is given appropriate attribution."""@en .

:MaterialComposition_batteryMaterials_batteryMaterials a owl:Class,
        aas:SubmodelElementCollection ;
    rdfs:label "BatteryMaterials"@en ;
    rdfs:comment """"Component materials used" (No. 17.a-c): Naming the materials (as a composition of substances) in cathode, anode, electrolyte according to public standards, including specification of the corresponding component (i.e., cathode, anode, or electrolyte). We suggest a reporting threshold of 0.1 % weight by weight.

DIN DKE Spec 99100 chapter reference: 6.5.3-6.5.4"""@en .

:MaterialComposition_hazardousSubstances_hazardousSubstances a owl:Class,
        aas:SubmodelElementCollection ;
    rdfs:label "HazardousSubstances"@en ;
    rdfs:comment """"Hazardous substances" (No 20.a-e): Name (agreed substance nomenclature, e.g. IUPAC or chemical name) all hazardous substance (as ?any substance that poses a threat to human health and the environment?). Suggested above 0.1 % weight by weight within each (sub-)component.

DIN DKE Spec 99100 chapter reference: 6.5.4 - 6.5.6"""@en .

